                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d298">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.115/117: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-01-15T18:00:00+08:00"
                            >January 15, 1938—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 15—4 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>86. Following from Tokyo: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“January 15, 5 p.m. Our January 10, 11 [<hi rend="italic">10</hi>]
                                a.m.<note n="16" xml:id="d298fn16">
                                <ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_564">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, Vol.
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 564</ref>.</note> The
                            Foreign Office informed us that the War Department has today informed
                            military authorities both at Shanghai and Nanking to refrain from
                            irregular entry of American property.</p>
                        <p>Please repeat to Nanking, Hankow, and Department. Grew.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Repeated to Hankow and Nanking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
